<div class="text-center">
  <h2>How to brew a delicious pot of coffee, anywhere at Turing!</h2>
  
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header">
        <h4 class="card-title">Blake</h4>
        <h6 class="card-meta">The Basement</h6>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <dl>
        <dt>
          1. Make sure the coffee pot and grounds basket are empty and rinsed out.
        </dt>
        <dt>
          2. Set grinder to medium (or one notch below).
        </dt>
        <dt>
          3. Grind beans and fill filter until it is just over half full.
        </dt>
        <dt>
          4. Check area on brewer where the basket will go for grounds. Clean if necessary!
        </dt>
        <dt>
          5. Put filter into basket. Place basket into brewer.
        </dt>
        <dt>
          6. Place coffee pot in its usual place.
        </dt>
        <dt>
          7. Press the start button (or equivalent).
        </dt>
        <dt>
          8. Let everyone know there's a new pot with <a href="/" class="how-to-page-link">/coffee_brewing Blake</a>! :)
        </dt>
      </dl>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header">
        <h4 class="card-title">Gusto</h4>
        <h6 class="card-meta">The Windows</h6>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <dl>
        <dt>
          1. Make sure the coffee pot is empty and rinsed out.
        </dt>
        <dt>
          2. Set grinder to medium (or one notch below).
        </dt>
        <dt>
          3. Grind beans and fill filter until it is just over half full.
        </dt>
        <dt>
          4. Fill white pitcher all the way with water.
        </dt>
        <dt>
          5. Place coffee pot under machine. (take out the spout insert if necessary)
        </dt>
        <dt>
          6. Fill machine with water from the pitcher.
        </dt>
        <dt>
          7. Brew coffee!
        </dt>
        <dt>
          8. Let everyone know there's a new pot with <a href="/" class="how-to-page-link">/coffee_brewing Gusto</a>! :)
        </dt>
        <dd>
          ps thanks to Maia for the Gusto-specific directions! 
        </dd>
      </dl>
    </div>
